    [ctns_front]
Slope-Intercept Form<br/>Linear Function
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The <strong>Slope-Intercept Form</strong> of a linear function is given by the equation,
$|y = mx + b,|$
for all $$x,y \in \mathbb{R}$$ and where $$m$$ is the slope of the line, and $$b$$ is the $$y$$-intercept.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]
